<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1923-08-28T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1923-08-28T14:00:00-05:00" n="489" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d489">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">711.1211/161: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Chargé in Mexico</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Summerlin</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1923-08-28T15:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">August 28,
                                        1923—3 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>124. Your 85, August 27, 3 P.M. It is entirely satisfactory to the
                            Department for Mr. Pani to release the statement embraced in the
                            subquotation of the Department’s 121 August 25, 6 P.M. simultaneously
                            with the Department on Friday August 31 at noon Washington time.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
